    "prompt": "According to the reading \"Mod02 FIRE Economics: Mod2HW\", what are the roles of public awareness campaigns in fire economics according to the text?",
    "response": "Public awareness campaigns play a vital role in fire economics by fostering community engagement and compliance with fire safety practices. These campaigns serve to educate the public about fire risks, prevention methods, and safety protocols that can be implemented to reduce the likelihood of fire hazards. In the context of diminishing returns, while initial campaigns may yield significant behavioral changes leading to improved fire safety, continued investments may result in less substantial additional changes as community awareness becomes saturated. Therefore, public information campaigns are seen as cost-effective tools in fire prevention strategies, especially when they succeed in effectively modifying community behaviors and enhancing safety awareness.",
