    "prompt": "According to the reading \"Mod02 FIRE Economics: Mod2HW\", how does the LCPL model determine the optimal investment effort (E*) in fire prevention?",
    "response": "The LCPL model determines the optimal investment effort (E*) in fire prevention by analyzing the balance between the costs of investment and the benefits of reduced fire losses. This is managed through calculating the marginal cost of investment against the marginal benefit derived from reduced risk of fire damage. The point where these two lines intersect indicates optimal investment, meaning that at this level, the additional cost of spending on fire prevention equals the additional benefit from avoided losses. This model helps planners make informed decisions on how much to invest to achieve the best outcomes in fire risk management.",
    "source_file": "C:\\Users\\wei\\OneDrive - Colostate\\Teaching\\NR444\\Mod02_FIRE_Economics\\Mod2HW.docx",
