    "response": "The LCPL model aids in identifying efficient fire investment strategies by providing a visual and analytical framework that equates the costs of fire prevention measures with the expected reductions in fire-related losses. By evaluating the marginal benefits of different investment levels versus their associated costs, the model enables practitioners to pinpoint the most efficient allocation of limited resources. It guides decision-makers towards finding the equilibrium point where returns on investment are maximized, ensuring that spending is directed toward strategies that produce the greatest reductions in fire risk. This systematic approach facilitates improved decision-making for budgeting in fire prevention.",
