    "response": "The first order condition for minimizing the total cost function requires that the absolute value of marginal damage is equal to the absolute value of marginal cost. This condition indicates that the optimal management effort level is reached when the slopes of the damage curve and the cost curve are equal in absolute terms, effectively implying that increased management effort should balance the cost of damage and management expenses.",
