    "prompt": "According to the reading \"Mod02 FIRE Economics: Mod2HW\", how does changing fire economics with respect to increasing or decreasing budget constraints affect fire management strategies?",
    "response": "Changing fire economics due to increasing or decreasing budget constraints significantly affects fire management strategies. When budgets are constrained, fire management must prioritize interventions that yield the most significant impact on fire prevention and firefighting efficiency, often leading to a focus on low-cost, high-return strategies. Conversely, when budgets increase, departments may be tempted to invest in higher-cost technologies and programs that have lower immediate returns or that still bring in diminished returns on investment. Therefore, fire departments need to be agile and adaptive, ensuring that budget adjustments are aligned with a consistent evaluation of risk management outcomes. Adopting flexible funding models focused on evidence-based practices remains essential.",
    "source_file": "C:\\Users\\wei\\OneDrive - Colostate\\Teaching\\NR444\\Mod02_FIRE_Economics\\Mod2HW.docx",
